cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DS 

This paper is about a new framework for Convolutional Neural Networks (CNNs) that uses domain knowledge to improve performance. The paper focuses on the application of this framework to image classification tasks, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under computer vision (cs.CV). Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical analysis of convergence and generalization errors, which suggests that it may also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of geometric operators in the framework suggests that it may also be categorized under neural networks (cs.NE) and data structures (cs.DS).
